article.headline: Nevada 62, Rice 59
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Ramon Sessions scored 15 points as Nevada stayed in first place in the Western Athletic Conference by beating Rice 62-59 Saturday. Nevada (14-4, 7-1 WAC) jumped out to a nine-point halftime lead and held on in the second half for its third straight win. Rice (10-5, 5-2) lost its first game at home this season-- dropping to 9-1. Michael Harris scored 19 points and grabbed 12 rebounds, and Jason McKrieth added 18 points for the Owls. The Wolf Pack, who jumped out to an 18-9 lead to open the game, led 34-25 at halftime. Rice opened the second half on 17-9 surge to pull within 43-42 midway through the second half. Nevada's Nick Fazekas had 11 points and 10 rebounds, and Kyle Shiloh and Kevinn Pinkney each had 10 points.
